  "local_port": 54806,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much does it cost to learn at Oxford aviation academy?",
  "response": "The cost of training at Oxford Aviation Academy (OAA), which is now part of **CAE Oxford Aviation Academy** after being acquired by CAE, can vary significantly depending on the type of program you're interested in. Here\u2019s a general overview of the costs associated with their training programs:\n\n### 1. **Pilot Training Programs**\n   - **Integrated ATPL (Airline Transport Pilot License):**  \n     The cost for an integrated ATPL program typically ranges from **\u00a380,000 to \u00a3100,000** (approximately $100,000 to $130,000 USD). This includes:\n     - Flight training\n     - Ground school\n     - Theoretical exams\n     - Type rating (if included)\n   - **Modular ATPL:**  \n     The modular route is often cheaper but can still cost **\u00a360,000 to \u00a380,000** ($75,000 to $100,000 USD), depending on the number of hours and modules you take.\n\n### 2. **Type Rating Courses**\n   - Type rating courses (e.g., for Boeing 737, Airbus A320, etc.) cost between **\u00a320,000 to \u00a330,000** ($25,000 to $38,000 USD) depending on the aircraft type and location.\n\n### 3. **Additional Costs**\n   - **Accommodation and Living Expenses:**  \n     These can vary widely depending on your location (UK or abroad) but typically range from **\u00a310,000 to \u00a315,000** per year.\n   - **Medical Exams and Licenses:**  \n     Initial medical exams and licensing fees can cost an additional **\u00a31,000 to \u00a32,000**.\n\n### 4. **Scholarships and Financing**\n   - Some airlines offer sponsorship or training bonds, which can help cover costs in exchange for a commitment to work with the airline after training.\n   - CAE Oxford Aviation Academy also offers financing options and scholarships for eligible candidates.\n\n### 5. **Other Programs**\n   - **Air Traffic Control Training:**  \n     Costs vary but typically range from **\u00a310,000 to \u00a320,000**.\n   - **Cabin Crew Training:**  \n     Costs are lower, usually **\u00a31,000 to \u00a33,000** depending on the program.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- Costs can vary depending on the location of the training center (UK, Europe, or other international locations).\n- Prices are subject to change, so it\u2019s best to contact CAE Oxford Aviation Academy directly for the most up-to-date and detailed information.\n\nFor precise pricing and program details, visit the official **CAE Oxford Aviation Academy** website or contact their admissions team.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
